-- Petrobras Buys Frere’s 50% Stake in Texas Refinery, Tijd Reports
-- B y   J e n n i f e r   M .   F r e e d m a n
-- 2012-07-04T07:14:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/petrobras-buys-frere-s-50-stake-in-texas-refinery-tijd-reports.html
Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4) , known as
Petrobras, paid $820.5 million for the Frere group’s 50 percent
stake in the Texas oil refinery Pasadena Refining Systems,
Belgian newspaper De Tijd reported.  The stake was held through energy trader Transcor Astra,
which is 80 percent owned by  Albert Frere ’s Cie. Nationale a
Portefeuille SA and 20 percent by its staff, according to the
newspaper, which didn’t say where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer M. Freedman in Geneva at 
 jfreedman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
